----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Purpose
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Frieve Editor is designed for uses such as the following.

- As an idea processor
  Place keyword cards that can spark ideas one after another on the screen.
  As new ideas come to you, place those on the screen as cards as well, add labels
  to classify them, and write their relationships to other keywords as links.
  The labels and links you add can then be used to arrange the cards automatically.
  Features such as randomly showing cards or randomly tracing links help support
  fresh and unconventional thinking.

- For concise description and organization of complex situations
  Write down complex situations whose conditions are intertwined, starting from
  whatever parts you already understand.
  By defining relationships with labels and links, you can describe complex matters
  more clearly. Doing so helps you discover solutions that take into account effects
  that are easy to overlook in everyday thinking. Even complicated ideas that were
  previously very hard to explain or share can be communicated naturally.

- As a project management tool
  Describe the tasks that need to be done, how they relate to one another, the order
  in which they should be performed, budgets, risks, and so on.
  With labels, each card can be classified as already completed, something that must
  be done immediately, something to postpone, and more. This makes it easier to judge
  what should be done next, what is likely to become a problem, and how the project
  should move forward.

- Other uses
  You can also use it for meeting minutes, personal notes, system descriptions,
  blog post drafts, and many other purposes.
40
Title: Key Features
Label:1
Fixed:0
