----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Key Features
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The main features of Frieve Editor are as follows.

- Representation with cards and links
  In Frieve Editor, each idea or fact is written on a single card, and the
  relationships between cards are expressed with links. Because links can be drawn
  from any card to any other card, even complex topics can be described naturally.

- Classification of cards and links with labels
  Each card and link can have multiple labels. Labels can be defined freely by the
  user. Because cards and links are color-coded by label on screen, you can grasp
  their meaning at a glance.

- Automatic arrangement and display filtering for cards
  Frieve Editor can automatically arrange card layouts based on the links attached to
  cards and the labels assigned to them. This makes it easy to view your information
  from different angles. You can also show or hide cards and links by label, or limit
  the visible range by number of links, so that only the information you need is shown.

- Animation
  Frieve Editor includes several animations to support idea generation and to help
  you understand what has been described.
  Animations that present created cards at random encourage new connections between
  different cards. Animations that trace links at random help you intuitively grasp
  how cards are related.
41
Title: Basic Features
Label:1
Fixed:0
X:0.19487227499485
Y:0.933239459991455
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:2023/04/14 20:14:08
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Basic Features
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Cards
  In Frieve Editor, one piece of writing is stored in one card.
  Whenever you think of something, create a card and write it down. To describe
  things efficiently, break a topic down into pieces as small as possible and
  describe it using many cards.

- Links
  Links define relationships between cards. A link can be drawn from one card to
  another card. Based on multiple links between cards, Frieve Editor can automatically
  arrange cards so that linked cards are placed near one another.

- Labels
  Frieve Editor lets you assign labels to both cards and links.
  By default, three labels are defined: Probrem (Problem), Solution, and Result,
  but labels can be edited freely.

  Assigning labels to cards helps you organize them efficiently. For example, you can
  automatically arrange cards so that cards with the same label are placed close to
  one another, show only cards with a certain label, or hide them. You can also group
  cards with the same label and display them as a single card.

  In the same way, labels attached to links can be used to show or hide only links
  with a certain label. Combined with automatic arrangement based on linked cards being
  placed close together, this makes it easy to reorganize cards while focusing on a
  particular kind of relationship.
277
