----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Version History
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

- 3.00 (2026/03/19)
  Added Auto Save / Auto Reload functionality.
  Improved wheel and gesture operations (wheel = scroll, Ctrl+wheel = zoom,
  Ctrl+Shift+wheel = font size, pinch = zoom).
  Added support for 13 languages (menu display and language-specific help files).
  Restored text-to-speech (TTS) functionality.
  Changed to the MIT license.
  Also made several small improvements and bug fixes:
    Optimized search speed.
    When the same file is already open in another instance, that instance is now activated.
    Fixed a bug with GPT model specification in setting2.ini.
    Fixed web search functionality.
    Fixed label button layout.

- 2.00 (2023/04/14)
  Added support for calling the ChatGPT API.

- 1.40 (2021/08/09)
  Made several small improvements and bug fixes.

- 1.32 (2013/11/02)
  Added support for newer versions of Windows.
  Added 64-bit support.
  Changed the default language to Japanese.
  Also made several small improvements and bug fixes.

- 1.31 (2008/09/07)
  Saving a file now stores the current coordinates and various settings, and loading
  the file restores them.
  Added curved links.
  Added HierarchicalText to File menu -> Export.
  Added string replacement for card names and body text (Edit menu -> Replace, Ctrl+R).
  Selected links now blink.
  Links related to the current card are now highlighted.
  Changed the shortcut for editing a card title from Ctrl+T to F2.
  Localized some messages that had not yet been translated into Japanese.
  Fixed a bug in the Statistics tab where the day of the week could shift.
  Fixed a bug that caused an error when editing body text on the right or bottom side
  of the Browser.
  Fixed a bug where using dotted lines could sometimes cause an error.
  Fixed a memory leak when displaying the Statistics tab.
  Fixed a memory leak when using Tree (Radial) auto-arrangement.

- 1.30 (2008/06/15)
  Added support for inserting simple drawings into cards (Drawing tab).
  Added statistical graph display such as label counts (Statistics tab).
  Added a function to link to all cards with a designated label (Insert menu).
  Added a function to add a designated label to all destination cards (Insert menu).
  Added Japanese localization for all windows (View menu -> Language).
  The status bar now shows the number of selected cards.
  Also made several small improvements and bug fixes.

- 1.23 (2008/04/15)
  You can now start typing a title directly without clicking a card first.
  The current selection is now used as the search key.
  Search keyword history is now saved.
  Zooming with the Page Up and Page Down keys is now supported.
  Selecting a link in the link list now moves Related Text.
  Improved the initial position of child and sibling cards when auto-arrangement is off.
  The body editor shown on the right or bottom of the Browser is now resizable.
  Fixed a bug on Windows 98 where right-clicking after selecting multiple lines caused
  an error.
  Fixed an issue where text being converted by the IME could fail to display.
  Fixed an issue where adding images or video by drag and drop was not reflected immediately.
  Fixed an issue where zooming with the mouse wheel could not reach the final zoom level.
  Fixed an issue where link-related settings were not saved.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.22 (2008/02/11)
  Added global search (list display of search results).
  Added internet search using selected text or card titles.
  Added support for inserting external links by drag and drop and creating cards with
  external links.
  Added Matrix (Index), which arranges cards neatly by card order.
  Added Find Previous (Edit menu -> Find Previous, Shift+F3).
  The Editor tab can now display the body text of linked cards (Related Text).
  You can now cut text from the body and create a linked card from the selected card.
  Added support for importing text in which hierarchy is represented with periods
  (File menu -> Import).
  Added Text Length to score display.
  Added Snow and Cherry Blossom to background animations.
  Selecting a card now scrolls immediately by default (this can be changed from
  View menu -> Others).
  Fixed a bug where F3 could search only card titles.
  Fixed an issue where the initial size of the link list under the editor was 0.
  Fixed an issue where Ctrl+click on an external link in the Editor tab sometimes
  did not open it.
  Fixed an issue where score type settings were not saved.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.21 (2007/12/01)
  Added hierarchical auto-arrangement (Tree(Radian); requires a root card).
  Added a file list for quickly opening files (move the mouse to the left side of
  the screen).
  Added Random Jump and Random Map animations.
  Added batch conversion of link direction (Edit menu -> Batch Conversion).
  Card list visibility can now be configured (View menu -> Others).
  The width of the card list and related settings are now saved when the program exits.
  Added support for specifying video playback position
  (start(ms)-end(ms)| before the file name).
  Cursor animation can now be turned on and off (View menu -> Others).
  Fixed a bug where double-clicking a link under the Editor tab did not follow it.
  Fixed a bug where titles could not be edited in the Browser while the editor was
  always visible.
  Fixed a bug where moving cards with the cursor canceled AutoZoom.
  Fixed a bug where hidden cards could be selected by range selection.
  Fixed a bug where Full Screen could not be toggled during animation.
  Fixed a bug where dragging on the Overview was not possible when anti-aliasing
  was enabled.
  Fixed a bug where pressing Ctrl+E while editing a card title in the Browser caused
  an error.
  Reduced screen flicker.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.20 (2007/11/04)
  Added Undo and Redo for up to 10 editing operations.
  Added multiple-card selection.
  Added cut, copy, and paste for cards.
  Added body editing in the Browser screen (View menu -> Text).
  Added search limited to currently visible cards.
  The current card is now marked with a visible cursor.
  Added background animation (View menu -> Others).
  Added Japanese localization for popup menus.
  Changed opening external links from Ctrl+click to Ctrl+Shift+click.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.13 (2007/10/15)
  Added various editing commands to the Browser right-click menu.
  Link style can now be changed.
  Added batch conversion of all card shapes and all link shapes (Edit -> Change Shape).
  Added default size, shape, and fixed-position settings for cards and links.
  Added ticker display of the first one or two lines of body text in the Browser.
  Added card shadow drawing.
  Added simple gradient display for cards.
  Added outline drawing for links.
  Added support for displaying video inside cards (enter a file name or URL in the body).
  Added support for importing hierarchical text and text files in folders (File menu -> Import).
  Added export of Browser images in BMP and JPEG formats (File menu -> Export).
  Added support for copying various data to the clipboard (File menu -> Export).
  Added anti-aliasing for Browser display (View menu -> Others).
  Included sample wallpapers in the wallpaper folder under the installation folder.
  Added various editing features in full-screen mode (move the mouse to the top of the screen).
  Fixed a bug where LinkLabel in some files was not loaded correctly.
  Fixed a bug where hexagonal cards were not drawn correctly.
  Fixed a bug where double-clicking a card in full screen caused an error.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.12 (2007/10/01)
  Fixed a bug where adding a card while Arrange ON and Zoom were active caused an error.
  Also made several small bug fixes.

- 1.11 (2007/09/30)
  Added fixed card positions (pushpin button).
  Added Arrange (Matrix), which arranges cards neatly in a grid.
  Added an overview of the whole card layout in the lower-right corner of the Browser.
  Cards can now be moved with the cursor keys in the Browser.
  Added Link Limitation that shows only cards linked in the reverse direction.
  Added Link Limitation that shows links between the current card and the target.
  Added a new card shape that draws a small figure at the center and hollows out the text.
  In addition to circles around cards with the same label, rectangles can now be drawn.
  The font can now be changed (View menu -> Font -> Change Font).
  Wallpaper can now be specified for the Browser screen (View menu -> Others).
  Added Soft arrangement modes that prioritize avoiding overlap.
  Card auto-arrangement now continues even while dragging.
  Auto-arrangement and scrolling are now slightly smoother.
  Added shortcuts for moving between Browser and Editor (Ctrl+B, Ctrl+E).
  Changed the highlight trigger for the three most recently viewed cards from Shift
  to Space.
  Changed the drag modifier for moving cards with the same label from Shift to Ctrl.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.10 (2007/09/01)
  Added a setting to wrap body text at the right edge via View menu -> Text -> WordWrap.
  Card titles can now contain line breaks using \n or Ctrl+Enter in the Browser.
  Added arrangement by title/body similarity (Similarity).
  Added Normalize, which zooms the layout so cards fit on screen.
  Added support for various score types (View menu -> Score).
  Added read-aloud for card titles (requires Microsoft Agent).
  Added case-insensitive search (leave Match Case unchecked).
  Fixed a bug where shortcut keys could not be used in the search dialog.
  Fixed an issue where an error could occur right after startup.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.05 (2007/08/03)
  Added Japanese menu selection via View menu -> Change Language.
  Added support for displaying images specified by external links on cards.
  Added score calculation and display via View menu -> Others.
  Added export of the card title list via File menu -> Export.
  Cards viewed more recently are now displayed in front.
  Pressing Shift now highlights the three most recently viewed cards.
  Label names are now displayed inside the label circles in the Browser.
  Expanded the Browser card layout area to four times the previous size
  (twice as wide and twice as tall).
  AutoZoom now always keeps related cards within the visible screen.
  File loading is now faster.
  Fixed an issue where cards could overlap during auto-arrangement.
  Fixed an issue where Delete could not remove a card immediately after editing its title.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.04 (2007/07/16)
  Added per-label card size settings with the View button on the Browser tab.
  Labels can now be enabled or disabled.
  Added filtering of visible cards by date.
  Added filtering of visible cards by minimum card size.
  Foreground and background colors can now be changed from View menu -> Others.
  Multiple cards can now be created at once from multi-line text, using each line as a title.
  The file name of the file being edited is now shown on the taskbar.
  When a card is selected, Cards now scrolls until the selected card is visible.
  Fixed a bug where the program could not start if no default printer existed.
  Fixed a bug where deleting a Link Label that was in use caused an error and left the
  application unusable.
  Fixed an issue where saving could fail under heavy load and the cursor remained as an
  hourglass.
  Fixed an issue where closing the search dialog returned the cursor position to the top
  of the page.
  Fixed an issue where clicking blank space while Fold was active could select a card.
  Fixed an issue where the selection range during search was incorrect.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.03 (2006/12/17)
  Added simple printing of the Browser display.
  Added Shift+Insert to create a parent-node card.
  Card shapes and sizes can now be changed.
  Added support for larger zoom levels.
  Added a status bar showing character counts and similar information
  (visibility can be changed from the View menu).
  Added Select All to the Edit menu.
  Fixed display corruption and file corruption when pasting RichText.
  Fixed a bug where deleting a link with the Delete key while dragging it caused an error.
  Fixed an issue where the line was not shown when dragging a labeled link.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.02 (2006/10/21)
  Added Insert to create a child-node card.
  Added Enter to create a sibling-node card.
  Added Insert while a link is selected to create a card between the linked cards.
  Links can now be edited by dragging.
  Added search limited to card titles or body text.
  Added card-title search from the Browser screen.
  Added Shift+drag to move cards with the same label together.
  Search is now faster.
  Display is now slightly faster.
  When creating a new card, the initial Index now changes depending on the card currently
  being edited.
  Fixed an issue where folded cards repelled too strongly during Arrange.
  Fixed an issue where Tab could not be inserted into the body.
  Also made several small bug fixes and improvements.

- 1.01 (2006/10/07)
  Card titles can now be edited directly in the Browser.
  Immediately after creating a new card, the program now enters title editing mode.
  Added Auto Zoom, which automatically zooms the Browser screen in or out.
  Added arrangement by card order (Index).
  View button -> Link Limitation can now limit by link direction.
  Added Cut to New Card Title to the Editor right-click menu.
  Added Shuffle, which randomizes card coordinates in the Browser.
  Added Shuffle (Edit -> Sort menu), which randomizes card order.
  Fixed a bug where clicking a card in the Browser could select the card underneath it.

- 1.00 (2006/09/24)
  Initial release.
24
