----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Frequently Asked Questions
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Q. Is there any way to make the Browser area larger?

A. In Arrange (automatic card layout) at the top of the Browser screen, select
Normalize and press the Arrange ON button. The cards will be arranged automatically
around the center of the Browser while preserving their relative positions.
After arranging, you can use the Zoom bar to zoom in or out, and you can change the
visible area of the Browser by clicking or dragging the scrollbars or the overview
display at the lower right of the Browser.


Q. Can Frieve Editor be started from a USB memory device or similar media?

A. Copy every file from the Frieve Editor installation folder
(normally c:\Program Files\Frieve Editor\) to the USB memory device.
You can then use Frieve Editor by running editor.exe there.
Frieve Editor does not use the registry.


Q. I would like to use Frieve Editor for work.

A. Frieve Editor is free for both personal and commercial use.
You do not need to contact us even if you deploy it widely.


Q. It seems to connect to the internet when it starts. What is it doing?

A. It is checking the update status of the latest Frieve Editor release.
This is the same operation as Help menu -> Check Latest Release.
You can also configure from Help menu -> Check Latest Release whether the newest
release should be checked automatically.
If you do not want it to connect, blocking it with a firewall or similar tool will
not cause any problem at all.


Q. Japanese text appears garbled in the Browser.

A. The font character set may be set to a non-Japanese option such as a Western
font set. Open the font dialog from View menu -> Font -> Change Font, choose a
Japanese font, and set the character set to Japanese.


Q. Video attached to a card will not play.

A. Try installing the codec introduced here:
http://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ffdshow
