-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Create a New Card
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Double-click any empty area in the Browser where no card is placed.

Note: In this case, the new card is added to the end of the card list.

Note: If you click the third button from the left at the top-left of the Browser
      screen (the button marked with L and a card), choose a label, and then
      double-click, you can add a card that already has that label assigned.

Or,

Select New Card from the Insert menu.

Note: In this case, the new card is added after the currently selected card.
      If no card is selected, it is added to the end of the card list.

Or,

1. Right-click in the Cards list on the left side of the screen.
2. Choose New Card from the menu that appears.

Note: In this case, the new card is added before the currently selected card.
      If no card is selected, it is added to the end of the card list.

Or,

1. In the Editor tab, select a portion of an existing card's body text that you
   want to use as the body of a new card.
2. Choose Cut to New Card from the Editor's right-click menu.
   A new card is created using the selected text as its body.

Or,

1. In the Editor tab, select the line or lines in an existing card's body that you
   want to use as the title of a new card
   (select multiple lines to create multiple cards at once).
2. Choose Cut to New Card Title or Cut to New Card Title with Link from the
   Editor's right-click menu. A new card is created using the selected text as
   its title. If you choose with Link, a link is also created from the original
   card to the newly created card.
57
Title: How to Create a Card Linked from an Existing Card
Label:2
Fixed:0
X:0.00704234046861529
Y:0.547152161598206
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Create a Card Linked from an Existing Card
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Select the source card in the Browser.
3. Press the Insert key. A new card linked from the selected card is created.

Note: In this case, the new card is added after the last card among the cards
      linked from the selected card.

Note: The labels of the selected card are inherited by the new card.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Select the source card in the Browser.
3. Press Shift+Insert. A new card linked to the selected card is created.

Note: In this case, the new card is added after the last card among the cards
      linked to the selected card.

Note: The labels of the selected card are inherited by the new card.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Select a card that is a sibling of the card you want to create.
3. Press Enter. A new card linked from the source card of the selected card is created.

Note: In this case, the new card is added after the currently selected card.

Note: If more than one card links to the selected card, the new card is created
      from the most recently selected of those source cards.

Note: The labels of the selected card are inherited by the new card.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Select the link where you want to insert a card.
3. Press the Insert key. A new card is created in the middle of the selected link.

Note: In this case, the new card is added after the last card among the cards
      linked from the source card of the selected card.
