Title: How to Edit Card Content with GPT
Label:2
Fixed:0
X:0.0822317451238632
Y:0.539448618888855
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:2023/04/14 20:17:39
Updated:2023/04/14 20:37:19
Viewed:2023/04/14 20:23:50
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Edit Card Content with GPT
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Choose GPT from the Edit menu, or press Ctrl+G on the keyboard.
   Using Ctrl+G is recommended.
2. Select the operation you want from the popup menu.
3. The first time you use it, enter your OpenAI API Key in the dialog box that appears.

Frieve Editor's GPT integration uses the paid, but extremely inexpensive, OpenAI API.
To use the OpenAI API, you need to create an OpenAI account and register a credit card.
For details on obtaining an OpenAI API Key, please refer to the OpenAI API website.
https://platform.openai.com/overview


The following operations are available by default.

Create
  Enter prompt instructions and generate new text based on them.
  You can use Japanese in the prompt as well.
  If no text is selected, text is generated from scratch.
  If text is selected, the generated result is based on both the selected text
  and your instruction.


Continue
  Generates text that continues from the current cursor position.

Simplify
  Replaces the selected text with a simpler version.

Longer
  Expands the selected text and replaces it with a longer version.

Summarize
  Summarizes the selected text.

Proofread
  Corrects grammar mistakes, typos, and similar issues in the selected text.

Translate to English
  Translates the selected text into English.

Translate to Japanese
  Translates the selected text into Japanese.


Title
  Generates a card title based on the selected text.


By editing setting2.ini, which is included with Frieve Editor, in a text editor,
you can add any ChatGPT integration features you want.

[GPTSystem]
SystemPrompt=Response should only be a single processing result. No additional explanations or excuses needed. Respond in the last language of the user's instructions without translating unless otherwise instructed by the user.
[GPT]
Create=Insert,(Input)
-=
Continue=InsertAfter, Generate text that follow the text below.
Simplify=Replace,Replace the text below with simpler text.
Longer=Replace,Inflate the text below and replace it with longer text than the original.
Summarize=Replace,Summarize and replace the following text.
Proofread=Replace,You are a professional multilingual proofreader. Replace the text below with the corrected text for grammar, misspellings, etc. If you do not need proofreading, please answer the original text as it is.
-=
Translate to English=Replace,Translate the following sentences into English.
Translate to Japanese=Replace,Translate the following sentences into Japanese.
-=
Title=Title,Create a title based on the following sentences.Responses should be in the original language.

[GPTSystem] SystemPrompt= is followed by the text used as the system instruction
for ChatGPT when every GPT integration feature is called.

Add any operation you like to each line under [GPT] in the following format.
OperationName=OperationType,Prompt that instructs the processing

Any text can be used as the operation name.
The operation name specified here is used for the popup menu shown when calling
the GPT feature.
If you add a line that says "-=", the menu is shown with a separator there.

Choose one of the following four operation types.

Insert
  Insert generated text at the current cursor position
InsertAfter
  Generate text based on the text up to the current cursor position and insert
  it at the current cursor position
Replace
  Replace the text in the current selection with generated text
Title
  Set the card title to text generated from the text in the current selection

Any text can be used as the prompt that instructs the processing.
You may also use Japanese in the prompt.
If you specify (Input), a dialog box opens after the operation is selected and
prompts the user to enter any prompt.
