----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Search for Cards
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Choose Find from the Edit menu, or press Ctrl+F.
2. Enter the search string in the dialog box that appears.
3. To search card titles, check Card Title.
4. To search the body text of cards, check Text.
5. To perform a case-sensitive search, check Match Case.
   To perform a case-insensitive search, clear Match Case.
6. To include cards hidden in the Browser in the search, check Invisible Card.
   If you do not want hidden cards included, clear Invisible Card.
7. Press Find Next.
8. To search for the next candidate using the same keyword and conditions,
   choose Find Next from the Edit menu or press F3.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Enter the search string in the edit box at the upper right of the Browser tab.
3. Press the Find button to the right of the edit box.
   This searches the currently visible cards for card titles that contain the
   search string.
