-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Display Images or Video on a Card
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Double-click the card you want to edit in the Browser, or double-click it in
   the Card list on the left side of the screen. If the card is already selected,
   click the Editor tab to display the Editor.
2. On one line in the card body, enter either the image file name (full path) or
   the URL of an image or video file.

Or,

1. Select the card to associate with the media.
2. Choose New Ext Link from the Insert menu.
3. Specify the image or video file.
   The specified file name is added as the last line of the card body.

Note: Supported image and video formats are currently bmp, jpg, avi, and mpg.

Note: If you write "playback start position (ms)-playback end position (ms)|"
      before the video file name or URL, the specified range will loop.
Example: 1000-5000|c:\movie.mpg
         Loops playback from 1 second to 5 seconds of c:\movie.mpg
73
Title: How to Display Drawings on a Card
Label:2
Fixed:0
X:0.057452104985714
Y:0.426572859287262
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Display Drawings on a Card
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Select the card into which you want to insert a drawing, either in the Browser
   or from the card list on the left side of the screen.
2. Click the Drawing tab to display the drawing editor.
3. Edit the drawing in the Drawing tab.
4. When you return to the Browser, the edited drawing is displayed on the card.


- To add a shape

1. At the upper left of the Drawing tab, click to choose the type of shape to add:
   freehand line, straight line, rectangle, or ellipse.
2. Drag the mouse inside the dotted frame to add the shape.


- To select a shape

1. At the upper left of the Drawing tab, choose the selection button with the
   mouse cursor icon.
2. Click the shape you want to select. Hold down Ctrl while clicking to toggle
   selection for multiple shapes, or drag over an area to select several shapes
   at once. To select all shapes, choose Select All from the Edit menu or from
   the right-click menu.


- To cut, copy, or delete a shape

1. Select the shape to edit.
2. Choose Cut, Copy, or Delete from the Edit menu or the right-click menu.
   You can also use the Delete key to delete it.


- To paste a cut or copied shape

Choose Paste from the Edit menu or the right-click menu.


- To resize a shape

1. Select the shape you want to resize.
2. Drag one of the small squares shown at the corners of the shape.


- To move a shape

1. Select the shape you want to move (multiple selection is allowed).
2. Drag any part of the shape other than the corner handles.


- To change the color of a shape

1. Select the shape.
2. Choose a color with Color.
   To use the card drawing color determined by labels, click Default.
   To choose another color, click the small button two positions to the right of
   Default and choose a color in the color selection dialog that appears.
   If the color you want has already been selected, you can simply click the color
   area immediately to the right of Default.
25
