----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Create a Link Between Cards
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Click the second button from the left at the top-left of the Browser tab
   (the button with a line on it) to select it.
3. Drag the mouse from the source card to the destination card.

Or,
1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Click the source card to select it.
3. While holding down Shift, click the destination card.
   You can create links quickly by continuing to click cards while holding Shift.

Note: If you click the fourth button from the left at the top-left of the Browser
      screen (the button marked with L and a line), choose a label, and then
      create a link, you can add a link with that label assigned by default.

Or,

1. Select the source card.
2. Choose New Link from the Insert menu.
3. Select the destination card in the dialog box that appears and press OK.

Or,

1. Select the source card.
2. Click the Editor tab.
3. Right-click in the link list at the bottom of the screen.
4. Choose New Link from the popup menu that appears.
5. Select the destination card in the dialog box that appears and press OK.
