-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Arrange Cards by Title/Text Similarity
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Click the Arrange ON button so that it is pressed.
3. Press the button to the right of the Arrange ON button and choose Similarity
   or Similarity(Soft) from the popup menu that appears.
4. To arrange cards using the latest similarity values, press the update button
   further to the right.

Caution: In projects without body text, similarity calculation finishes in a few
seconds, but if the number of cards reaches the thousands or the file is centered
on body text, similarity calculation may take a long time. For example, if the
body text size reaches about 500 kB, the calculation can take about one minute on
a CPU around 2 GHz.

Note: Because similarity calculation takes time, Frieve Editor calculates similarity
      between cards only once when Similarity is selected while the ON button is
      pressed, or when the ON button is pressed while Similarity is selected.
      After card titles or body text are edited, press the update button to rearrange
      cards using similarity values that reflect those edits.

Note: Compared with Similarity, Similarity(Soft) gives higher priority to preventing
      cards from overlapping.
46
Title: How to Arrange Cards Hierarchically
Label:5
Fixed:0
X:0.468564659357071
Y:0.998640239238739
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Arrange Cards Hierarchically
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Click the card that will become the root (the top of the hierarchy) to select it.
3. Turn on the root designation button on the screen
   (to the right of the pushpin button and to the left of the label).
4. Click the Arrange ON button so that it is pressed.
5. Press the button to the right of the Arrange ON button and choose Tree (Radial)
   from the popup menu that appears.

To change the order of cards within the same level, use the Up/Down buttons at the
upper right of the card list on the left side of the screen, or drag cards up and
down in the Browser.

To edit the hierarchy itself, drag links in the Browser and reconnect them.

To hide the lower levels under a specific card, press the "-" button shown at the
lower right of the card. To show a hidden level again, press the "+" button shown
at the lower right of the card.

Caution: When auto-arrangement is performed with Tree (Radial), card Index values
are forcibly sorted into hierarchy order.

Note: A card designated as a root shows ">" to the left of its title in the card
      list on the left side of the screen.

Note: When auto-arrangement is performed with Tree (Radial), the card list on the
      left side of the screen is displayed with indentation that matches hierarchy
      levels.

Note: If multiple cards are set as roots, multiple trees rooted at those cards are
      arranged on screen at the same time.
21
