Title: How to Choose Which Cards and Links Are Shown in the Browser
Label:5
Fixed:0
X:0.69487738609314
Y:0.919996082782745
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Choose Which Cards and Links Are Shown in the Browser
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Click the VIEW button on the screen. The VIEW dialog for choosing which cards
   and links to display appears.
3. Click either the Label tab or the Limitation tab.


- To limit visible cards by card size

1. Check Size Limitation.
2. Use the slider to the right of Size Limitation to specify the minimum size of
   cards to display.


- To limit visible cards by the number of links from the selected card

1. Check Link Limitation.
2. Use the Link Limitation slider to specify the link limit.
3. To further limit the result by link direction while using this setting, check Direction.
4. To limit to forward direction, check Forward. To limit to reverse direction, check Backward.
5. To add a restriction by target card, press the button to the right of Target Card,
   choose Select, and select the target card in the dialog box.
   Or, in the Browser, hold down Alt while clicking the target card.
   To clear the target-card restriction, press the button to the right of Target Card
   and choose No Assign.


- To limit visible cards by date

1. Check Date Limitation.
2. In Date Type, choose the date to use for the restriction.
   Created is the date and time the card was created, Edited is the date and time the
   card body was last edited, and Viewed is the date and time the card was last selected
   or shown.
3. In Date Limitation Type, choose how the restriction is applied.
   Old shows cards in order from oldest, New shows cards in order from newest,
   Near shows cards with dates close to the currently selected card, Older shows cards
   that are older than the selected card and close in date, and Newer shows cards that
   are newer than the selected card and close in date.
2. Use the slider to the right of Date Limitation to specify the strength of the restriction.
   With Old, the oldest cards are shown when the slider is at the left, and newer cards
   are added as you move it right.
   With New, the newest cards are shown when the slider is at the right, and older cards
   are added as you move it left.
   With Near, Older, and Newer, moving the bar to the right relaxes the restriction.


- To show or hide cards with labels

1. To show cards with certain labels, specify those labels in the Show column under Label.
   If a card has one or more of the checked labels, it is shown.
2. To hide cards with certain labels, specify those labels in the Hide column.
   If a card has one or more labels checked there, it is hidden.
   Hide settings take priority over show settings.


- To show or hide links with labels

1. To show links with certain labels, specify those labels in the Show column under
   Link Label. If a link has one or more of the checked labels, it is shown.
2. To hide links with certain labels, specify those labels in the Hide column.
   If a link has one or more labels checked there, it is hidden.
   Hide settings take priority over show settings.
28
Title: How to Sort Cards
