----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Zoom the Browser
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Check Auto Zoom at the upper right of the Browser tab.
   While Auto Zoom is checked, each time you select a card or link, the Browser
   automatically zooms so that the selected card or link and related cards fit on screen.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Drag the Zoom control on the Browser tab.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Hold down Ctrl and use the mouse wheel to zoom in and out.

Or,

1. Click the Browser tab.
2. Pinch/stretch on a touchpad to zoom in and out.
34
Title: How to Move Between Cards with the Keyboard
Label:6
Fixed:0
X:0.862526595592499
Y:0.718110978603363
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Move Between Cards with the Keyboard
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Press the arrow keys.
This moves to the card nearest to the current card, regardless of links.

Or,

Press Ctrl+Up or Ctrl+Down.
These move to the most recently shown parent card or child card, respectively.

Or,

Press Ctrl+Left or Ctrl+Right.
These move to sibling cards counterclockwise or clockwise, respectively.

Or,

Press Shift+arrow keys.
Among the cards linked to the current card, this moves to the one nearest to the
current card.
27
