Title: How to Show Cards Randomly
Label:6
Fixed:0
X:0.992111325263977
Y:0.654013574123383
Size:100
Shape:2
Visible:1
Created:1899/12/30
Updated:1899/12/30
Viewed:1899/12/30
-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to Show Cards Randomly
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Choose Random Flash, Random Map, Random Scroll, or Random Jump from the Animation
   menu. The animation starts and the Random Animation dialog appears.
   Random Flash displays the specified number of cards one after another.
   Random Map displays a random card, then expands the display to cards linked from it.
   Random Scroll scrolls the specified number of cards across the screen.
   Random Jump makes the specified number of cards bounce up from the bottom of the screen.
2. To zoom in or out, change Zoom.
3. To change the display speed, adjust Speed.
4. To change how many cards are shown on the screen at once, adjust Cards.
5. To enter or leave full-screen mode, press the Full Screen button or F10.
6. To pause or resume the animation, press the Pause button.
7. To end the animation, press the Stop button.
23
