-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
How to View Statistics
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

1. Click the Statistics tab.
   Initially, a graph showing the number of cards for each label is displayed.
2. To change the key used for the graph display, click the button to the right of Key
   and choose one of the following.

   Label: Displays a graph of the number of cards for each label (default)
   Number of Link: Displays a graph of the number of cards for each link count
   Created Date: Displays a graph of the number of cards by creation date and time
   Edited Date: Displays a graph of the number of cards by last edited date and time
   Viewed Date: Displays a graph of the number of cards by viewed date and time

   If Created Date, Edited Date, or Viewed Date is selected, you can also choose the
   aggregation unit from Year, Month, Day, Week, or Hour.

3. To list the cards included in each graph, click a bar in the graph.
   A list of included cards appears on the right side of the screen.


Note: This feature can also be used to list only cards that have a specific label.
15
