-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
File Menu
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

New
  Creates a new project.

Open
  Opens a saved project.

Save
  Overwrites the current project.

SaveAs
  Saves the current project with a new name.

Auto Save (This File)
  Toggles automatic saving on or off for this file.
  When enabled, changes are automatically saved after a period of inactivity.
  On application exit, unsaved changes are saved without a confirmation dialog.

Auto Reload (This File)
  Toggles automatic reloading on or off for this file.
  When enabled, the file is automatically reloaded when modified externally.
  However, automatic reloading does not occur while unsaved changes exist in the application.


Recent Files
  Opens a project that was used before.

Recent Folders
  Opens a project from a folder that was used before.


Import
  Loads data from files other than fip files.
  Txt File loads one or more text files as one card each.
  Hierarchical Text File loads a hierarchical text file whose leading indentation is
  made with tabs or spaces, using one line per card.
  Hierarchical Text File 2 loads a hierarchical text file in which the hierarchy is
  represented by the number of leading periods and the remaining text becomes the body.
  Text Files in a Folder loads all text files under a specified folder together with
  the folder structure.


Export
  Exports data to external files.
  Txt file(Card Title) outputs all card titles to a single text file.
  Txt file(Text) outputs the body text of all cards to a single text file.
  Txt files outputs each card as a separate text file. In that case, each file name is
  the card title plus ".txt".
  html files outputs the data in HTML format for browsing on the web.
  In addition to the file with the specified name, "cards.html" and files named
  card number + ".html" are created.
  Hierarchical Text outputs a text file in which hierarchy is represented by the number
  of leading periods. Hierarchical text exported in this format can be imported with
  Import menu -> Hierarchical Text File 2.

Caution: When performing Export operations that create multiple files, if files with
  the same names already exist, they are overwritten without warning.


Print Image
  Performs simple printing of the Browser display.
  The current Browser view is scaled to the selected paper size and printed.


Exit
  Exits Frieve Editor.
