----------------------------------------------------------------------------
View Menu
----------------------------------------------------------------------------

Font
  Changes the font.
  Default Size restores the standard size, Magnify enlarges it, and Reduce makes it smaller.
  To change the font family itself, choose Change Font and specify the font.

Card
  Changes card display settings.
  Shadow toggles card shadows on or off.
  Gradation toggles card gradients on or off.
  Ticker toggles ticker display of body text on cards. 1Line displays the first line
  of the card body, and 2Lines displays the first and second lines as ticker text.
  Image toggles thumbnail display of images on or off. The first jpg or bmp file written
  in the card body is used.
  Video toggles video display on or off. The first mpg or avi file written in the card body
  is used. Video display takes priority over image display.
  Drawing toggles drawing display on or off. Drawing display takes priority over image
  and video display.
  32x32 to 320x320 specifies the maximum size of images, video, and drawings shown on cards.
  Media larger than that is reduced so it fits within the specified size.

Link
  Changes link display settings.
  Link toggles link lines, Hemming toggles link outlines, Direction toggles link direction,
  and Name toggles link-name display on or off.

Label
  Changes label display settings.
  Circle toggles circles that show groups of the same label on or off.
  Rectangle toggles rectangles that show groups of the same label on or off.
  Name toggles label-name display on or off.

Text
  Changes body-text display settings.
  Text toggles display of the selected card's body text in the Browser.
  Centering toggles centered display or top-left display of body text in the Browser.
  Edit In Browser toggles whether double-clicking a card in the Browser edits its body in place.
  Always Show Editor toggles whether the editor is always shown in the Browser
  (effective with any setting except Under the Card).
  Under the Card edits the body immediately below the card.
  Browser Right edits the body at the right edge of the Browser.
  Browser Bottom edits the body at the bottom of the Browser.

Score
  Score toggles score display on or off.
  Authenticity calculates a score in which cards linked from high-score cards become
  higher in score.
  StartingPoint gives higher scores to source cards.
  Destination gives higher scores to destination cards.
  Links(Out) uses the number of outgoing links from a card.
  Links(In) uses the number of incoming links to a card.
  Links(Total) uses the total number of links on a card.
  Links(In-Out) uses incoming links minus outgoing links.
  Text Length uses the length of the body text.

Read Aloud
  Read Aloud toggles reading card titles aloud on or off.

Note: Microsoft Agent must be installed to read card titles aloud.
      This menu is not shown in environments where Microsoft Agent or the related
      speech components are not installed.

Note: Microsoft Agent is distributed free of charge by Microsoft, but its download
      addresses and required files appear to change frequently.
      If you need the read-aloud feature, please rely on information on the web and
      install the necessary files.

Others
  Changes other display-related settings.
  Card List toggles the card list on the left side of the screen on or off.
  File List toggles the file list shown when the mouse is moved to the left side
  of the screen on or off.
  Overview toggles the overview display at the lower right of the Browser on or off.
  FourgroundColor changes the foreground color, and BackgroundColor changes the background color.
  Wallpaper specifies a wallpaper. To clear the wallpaper, choose Wallpaper again.
  Fix Wallpaper fixes the wallpaper to fill the screen.
  Tile Wallpaper tiles the wallpaper across the whole Browser area.
  Background Animation toggles background animation on or off.
  Background Animation Type changes the kind of background animation.
  Cursor Animation toggles cursor animation on or off.
  No Scroll Lag toggles whether auto-scroll happens immediately when a card is selected.
  Anti-Aliasing toggles anti-aliasing on or off.
  2x performs anti-aliasing at twice the vertical and horizontal resolution, and 4x uses four times.

Change Language
  Changes the menu language (currently English and Japanese are supported).
  To support other languages, place a .lng file in the Frieve Editor folder
  (text-file format; see Japanese.lng for the format).


Full Screen
  Toggles full-screen display of the Browser.


Status Bar
  Toggles the status bar on or off.
